result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher T. Hayden was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court informs defendant nearing end of probation with unpaid court ordered obligations.  Court can extend probation.  Defendant informs he's been out of work, due for back surgery...  He informs that at his hearing in Buffalo Co. his probation was extended to end of August.  Court makes an exception in your case and enter judgment, tax intercept, collection and informs defendant to pay his restitution on Buffalo Co. case.  Court informs defendant to send him a letter the end of the month on the status.
Probation review hearing on July 2, 2018 at 02:15 pm.

records.descr: Notice of court ordered financial obligations

records.addlTxt: Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court, w/o counsel.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Here on Probation Review Hrg. due to unpaid court ordered obligations and nearing discharge.  State relays letter sent by DOC agent to court, Mr. Hayden paid and the State took those funds and applied to restitution on another case; relies on the PO agent's suggestion.  Mr. Hayden confirms he received a copy of the agent's letter.  Court extends probation for 8 months, if pay early, probation can ask for early discharge.

Probation review hearing on January 16, 2018 at 10:00 am.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court with attorney S. Joseph Randtke.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing after motion to revoke DPA in 15CF47 and Probation Review Hrg. in 16CM02 for failure to complete community service.  P&P Agent informs defendant didn't follow through with LE Phillips treatment program and he will need to finish that program.  Court withholds sentence and places defendant on 3 yrs probation in 15CF47; 30 days in the PCJ w/work release report 12/26 at 6:00 p.m.; pay costs; comply with any assessment or treatment set up by P&P; no possession or consumption of alcohol; no other illegal activity; advised of felony prohibitions; appeal rights.
Sentencing hearing on December 19, 2016 at 11:30 am.

Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court with attorney S. Joseph Randtke.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Motion hearing to revoke DPA and Probation Review Hrg.  Defendant agrees he did not complete community service.  Court finds grounds exists.  State's closing arguments.  Defendant addresses the Court.  Court revokes the DPA, find you guilty of burglary.  No request by counsel for PSI.  Referred to scheduling clerk for sentencing hrg. in 15CF47 and PRH on the other matter.
Probation review hearing on November 29, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court with attorney S. Joseph Randtke.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Motion to Revoke DPA.  Counsel confirms receipt of Motion, opposes motion and requests more time.  Referred to scheduling clerk.
Motion hearing on October 18, 2016 at 02:45 pm.

Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Hearing on defendant failed to complete C/S, terminated from the program and State's motion to revoke felony DPA.  Court advises defendant of right to attorney.  Matter adjourned to allow defendant to contact an attorney, informed to contact the SPD office before leaving today to see if qualifies for an attorney.  Motion hearing scheduled for September 20, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
Letter from defendant requesting to sit jail time for his community service.
Probation review hearing on September 12, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Buffalo-Pepin Counties CJCC Termination of C/S.  Buffalo-Pepin Counties CJCC Termination of C/S for failure to comply with the program.  The defendant has not completed the assigned community service.

Defendant Christopher T. Hayden in court with attorney Patrick William Waters.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement reached. Defendant will plead to count 1 in 15CF47 as DAGPA, and to newly filed charges in 16CM02, joint recommendation 2 yrs. probation, 10 days jail, 5 days credit.  State will dismiss 15CF51.  Court advises defendant of charge of burglary in 15CF47/max penalties; to charge of misdemeanor theft in 16CM02/max penalties and criminal tresspass/max. penalties. Defendant enters pleas of no contest to each count.  Plea Colloquy.  State moves to rescind motion to revoke bond in 15CF47, dismiss 15CF51.  Court finds defendant guilty of 2 counts in 16CM02, withholds sentence and places defendant on 2 yrs. probation w/conditions:  10 days in PCJ w/credit for 5 days com. 2/25 at 6 p.m.; comply with any assessment or counseling as set up by P&P; cooperate w/any drug testing as requested by DA or P&P; provide a DNA sample; costs on count 1 of $443; waive costs on count 2 and pay within 1st 18 mos. of probation; complete 80 hrs. community service monitored by C/S coordinator; Dismiss 15CF51; advised of appeal rights; motion to revoke bond w/drawn; bond vacated.
